Step 1 — Navigate to the Parent BP table

Open Power Apps maker portal: https://make.powerapps.com
Pick the EMS environment.
Left nav → Tables (under Dataverse).
Find and click into Parent Business Process (tenant display may show "Business Process" if singular).
You should see existing columns including pei_owningbu (added April 30, L1-A06).


Step 2 — Add the new column

Click + New → Column (top of the columns list).
Fill the side panel:

Display name:
Owning BU Manual Override

CRITICAL — expand Advanced options and set the schema name explicitly:

Name (schema name — under Advanced options):
owningbumanual
(Power Platform will prepend the pei_ publisher prefix automatically — final logical name: pei_owningbumanual. Do NOT type pei_ yourself; the maker portal adds it.)

Data type:

Yes/No
(In the dropdown: Choice → Yes/No)

Required:

Optional

Searchable: Yes (default; leave as-is)
Default value:

No
(In the Yes/No default selector — pick No, not Yes. This means new BPs default to not having override active.)

Enable auditing. Scroll down in the side panel → Advanced options → Enable auditing → toggle ON.
Description (helps future implementers — paste this in the Description field):

When Yes, Flow 1 will skip BU resolution for this Parent BP and preserve any existing Owning BU value. Use this when a BP's BU assignment differs from what the BP-to-BU mapping table would resolve. Symmetric with pei_owningbumanual on Application (ADR-036).

Verify everything before clicking Save — re-check Name field shows owningbumanual (lowercase, no pei_ prefix typed by you), Type is Yes/No, Default is No, Audit is ON.
Save.


Step 3 — Add to main form
The field needs to be on the form so users can see/edit it.

From the Parent Business Process table view → Forms tab.
Open the Information form (main form — same one Owning BU was added to per L1-A06).
Drag Owning BU Manual Override from the right-side column palette onto the form, immediately below the existing Owning BU field.
Save the form.
Publish the form (button next to Save).


Step 4 — Add to main view

Back on the Parent Business Process table → Views tab.
Open Active Parent Business Processes (main view).
Add Owning BU Manual Override column. Position it immediately after Owning BU.
Save and Publish the view.


Verify before saying "done"

 New column exists on Parent BP table
 Display name: Owning BU Manual Override
 Logical name (visible in column properties): pei_owningbumanual — all lowercase after the pei_ prefix (not pei_OwningBUManual — case matters; the lookup must be lowercase to match the L1-A07 pattern)
 Type: Yes/No
 Default: No
 Audit: ON
 Description filled in
 Added to the Information form, positioned below Owning BU
 Added to Active Parent Business Processes view, after Owning BU
 Form and view both published (not just saved)

Reply "done" when verified. I'll update the schema doc in the same step you confirm, per Schema Discipline.
